<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="156" pageId="2" pageNumber="155" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1127,1069,1573]" box="[151,667,1069,1094]" pageId="2" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,1069,1093]" pageId="2" pageNumber="155">Description.</emphasis>
Coloration entirely sienna (
<figureCitation box="[588,651,1069,1094]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[151,190,1571,1590]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,215,1494]" captionTargetId="figure-10@4.[151,1127,215,1503]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 1-6. Habitus. 1 – Sparedrus karenorum sp. nov., holotype. 2 – S. malickyi sp. nov., holotype. 3 – S. chiangmaiensis sp. nov., holotype. 4 – S. tryznai taunnguensis Švihla, 2006, paratype. 5 – S. sasajii nom. nov., holotype. 6 – S. rufus (Pic, 1922), syntype. (Photo J. Macek)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328201/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="155">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1127,1069,1573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="155">
Male. Eyes large, protruding, head across eyes moderately wider than pronotum, nearly parallel-sided behind eyes. Frons between eyes moderately wider than length of antennomere 2. Last palpomere of maxillary palpus securiform as in 
<figureCitation box="[727,804,1165,1190]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="7.[113,152,1547,1566]" captionTargetBox="[124,1066,520,1497]" captionTargetId="figure-100@7.[113,1085,512,1497]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs. 14-22. 14-15. Last maxillary palpomere of male. 14 – Sparedrus karenorum sp. nov.; 15 – S. rufus (Pic, 1922). 16-18. Antennomeres 2-3. 16 – S. karenorum sp. nov.,J; 17 – ditto,♀; 18 – S. atricolor (Pic, 1935),♀. 19-20.Apex of pygidium of female. 19 – S. atricolor; 20 – S. subserratus (Gressitt, 1939). 21-22. Antennomeres 9-10 of female. 21 – S. latipennis (Pic, 1923); 22 – S. angustatus (Pic, 1923). 23-24. Structure of elytra. 23 – S. chiangmaiensis sp. nov. 24 – S. malickyi sp. nov. Scale a – Figs. 16-22; b – Figs. 14-15." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328207/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="155">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
. Antenna reaching elytral apex (
<figureCitation box="[159,220,1197,1222]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[151,190,1571,1590]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,215,1494]" captionTargetId="figure-10@4.[151,1127,215,1503]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 1-6. Habitus. 1 – Sparedrus karenorum sp. nov., holotype. 2 – S. malickyi sp. nov., holotype. 3 – S. chiangmaiensis sp. nov., holotype. 4 – S. tryznai taunnguensis Švihla, 2006, paratype. 5 – S. sasajii nom. nov., holotype. 6 – S. rufus (Pic, 1922), syntype. (Photo J. Macek)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328201/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="155">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), antennomere 3 almost four times as long as antennomere 2 (
<figureCitation box="[881,959,1197,1221]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="7.[113,152,1547,1566]" captionTargetBox="[124,1066,520,1497]" captionTargetId="figure-100@7.[113,1085,512,1497]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs. 14-22. 14-15. Last maxillary palpomere of male. 14 – Sparedrus karenorum sp. nov.; 15 – S. rufus (Pic, 1922). 16-18. Antennomeres 2-3. 16 – S. karenorum sp. nov.,J; 17 – ditto,♀; 18 – S. atricolor (Pic, 1935),♀. 19-20.Apex of pygidium of female. 19 – S. atricolor; 20 – S. subserratus (Gressitt, 1939). 21-22. Antennomeres 9-10 of female. 21 – S. latipennis (Pic, 1923); 22 – S. angustatus (Pic, 1923). 23-24. Structure of elytra. 23 – S. chiangmaiensis sp. nov. 24 – S. malickyi sp. nov. Scale a – Figs. 16-22; b – Figs. 14-15." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328207/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="155">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
), antennomeres 3-10 more or less serrate with arcuate inner margin and with protruding inner lateroapical corner, antennomeres 6-11 more or less flattened dorsoventrally, more or less curved. Surface of frons and vertex punctate, covered by sparse, long, yellowish white semierect pubescence, semilustrous. Pronotum one fifth longer than wide, very slightly cordiform, moderately ovally depressed in its posterior half, its anterior margin widely rounded, anterior corners rounded, lateral margins moderately sinuate, posterior corners obtuse, posterior margin rounded. Surface of pronotum punctate and pubescent like that of head, semilustrous. Elytra parallel-sided, their surface punctate and pubescent like that of vertex and pronotum, semilustrous, elytral nervation absent. Last tergite exceeding last sternite by ca. one third, apex with triangular emargination, apex of last sternite widely triangularly emarginate. Tegmen only moderately shorter than aedeagus, aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[556,635,1549,1573]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="9.[113,152,830,849]" captionTargetBox="[134,1066,225,792]" captionTargetId="figure-242@9.[113,1088,204,802]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs. 25-29. Aedeagus, ventral view. 25 – Sparedrus karenorum sp. nov.; 26 – S. malickyi sp. nov.; 27 – S. chiangmaiensis sp. nov.; 28 – S. tryznai taunnguensis Švihla, 2006; 29 – S. rufus (Pic, 1922), with apex of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328209/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="155">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,219,531]" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">Female. Frons between eyes wider than in male, almost twice as long as antennomere 2, antenna shorter, reaching ca. three fourth of elytral length, emarginations of both last tergite and last sternite shallower.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,219,531]" box="[144,452,309,340]" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">
Length (J 
<specimenCount box="[248,272,309,340]" pageId="3" pageNumber="156" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
). 10.6-12.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="156" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,219,531]" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,359,347,371]" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Švihla &amp; Dejean, 2007" authorityName="Švihla &amp; Dejean" authorityYear="2007" box="[363,590,349,372]" class="Insecta" family="Oedemeridae" genus="Sparedrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="karenorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[363,590,349,372]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">Sparedrus karenorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[595,675,348,371]" pageId="3" pageNumber="156" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName box="[828,941,349,372]" class="Insecta" family="Oedemeridae" genus="Sparedrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unicolor">
<emphasis box="[828,941,349,372]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">S. unicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group as defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="SVIHLA V." box="[262,430,379,404]" pageId="3" pageNumber="156" pagination="1 - 35" refId="ref8285" refString="SVIHLA V. 2006 b: A revision of the genus Sparedrus (Coleoptera: Oedemeridae) from central part of the Palaearctic Region and from western part of the Oriental Region. Folia Heyrovskyana, Series A 14: 1 - 35." type="journal article" year="2006">ŠVIHLA (2006b)</bibRefCitation>
. It is related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Svihla, 2006" authorityName="Svihla" authorityYear="2006" box="[596,862,379,404]" class="Insecta" family="Oedemeridae" genus="Sparedrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alesivani">
<emphasis box="[596,719,381,404]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">S. alesivani</emphasis>
Švihla, 2006
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[877,946,379,403]" name="Nepal" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">Nepal</collectingCountry>
), from which it differs by the absence of small, seriate, impunctate and glabrous areas on elytra and by the slightly wider and more parallel-sided aedeagus in ventral view (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="SVIHLA V." box="[840,991,443,468]" pageId="3" pageNumber="156" pagination="1 - 35" refId="ref8285" refString="SVIHLA V. 2006 b: A revision of the genus Sparedrus (Coleoptera: Oedemeridae) from central part of the Palaearctic Region and from western part of the Oriental Region. Folia Heyrovskyana, Series A 14: 1 - 35." type="journal article" year="2006">ŠVIHLA 2006b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
